Available Tools: grep_file | grep_recursive | grep_case_insensitive | grep_count
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "pattern": "string", "path": "string", "flags": "string" }
Response Schema: { "matches": [{ "file": "string", "line": "number", "text": "string" }], "count": "number" }
---
Question: Find all occurrences of "error" in /var/log recursively with line numbers.
Call: { "func_call": "grep_recursive", "pattern": "error", "path": "/var/log", "flags": "-n" }
Response: { "matches": [{ "file": "/var/log/syslog", "line": 1024, "text": "Oct 12 10:00:01 server kernel: [error] disk read failure" }, { "file": "/var/log/auth.log", "line": 55, "text": "Oct 12 09:15:22 server sshd: error: PAM: Authentication failure" }], "count": 2 }

Question: Search for "TODO" in ~/projects ignoring case and showing line numbers.
Call: { "func_call": "grep_recursive", "pattern": "TODO", "path": "~/projects", "flags": "-i -n" }
Response: { "matches": [{ "file": "~/projects/src/main.py", "line": 45, "text": "# TODO: Refactor this function" }, { "file": "~/projects/docs/readme.md", "line": 12, "text": "## Todo List" }, { "file": "~/projects/tests/test_utils.py", "line": 88, "text": "# todo: add edge case tests" }], "count": 3 }

Question: Count how many times "password" appears in /etc recursively, case-insensitive.
Call: { "func_call": "grep_count", "pattern": "password", "path": "/etc", "flags": "-i -r" }
Response: { "matches": [], "count": 14 }

Question: Recursively find "connection timeout" in /var/log with line numbers.
Call: { "func_call": "grep_recursive", "pattern": "connection timeout", "path": "/var/log", "flags": "-n" }
Response: { "matches": [{ "file": "/var/log/nginx/error.log", "line": 304, "text": "2023/10/12 14:20:05 [error] connection timeout upstream" }], "count": 1 }

Question: Search for "import os" in ~/projects recursively with line numbers.
Call: { "func_call": "grep_recursive", "pattern": "import os", "path": "~/projects", "flags": "-n" }
Response: { "matches": [{ "file": "~/projects/src/app.py", "line": 3, "text": "import os" }, { "file": "~/projects/scripts/deploy.py", "line": 5, "text": "import os" }, { "file": "~/projects/tests/setup.py", "line": 2, "text": "import os" }], "count": 3 }

