Question: Find "404" in /var/log recursively with line numbers.
Call: { "func_call": "grep_recursive", "pattern": "404", "path": "/var/log", "flags": "-n" }
Response: { "matches": [{ "file": "/var/log/nginx/access.log", "line": 5001, "text": "192.168.1.5 - - [12/Oct/2023:15:00:00 +0000] \"GET /missing.html HTTP/1.1\" 404 162" }, { "file": "/var/log/apache2/error.log", "line": 33, "text": "[Fri Oct 12 15:01:00 2023] [error] File not found: 404" }], "count": 2 }
